Returns a mutable array reference to the last `N` items in the slice.

If the slice is not at least `N` in length, this will return `None`.

# Examples

```
let x = &mut [0, 1, 2];

if let Some(last) = x.last_chunk_mut::<2>() {
    last[0] = 10;
    last[1] = 20;
}
assert_eq!(x, &[0, 10, 20]);

assert_eq!(None, x.last_chunk_mut::<4>());
```
